postcontent:
I have a new and unfired high end "2 Vets" brand M4 AR 15 for sale. They are a Veteran owned company that produces high end AR's that are 100% US made parts and are made 100% here in the USA. This is an easier side charging carbine which makes this one especially well suited for practical/tactical and home defense. Instead of the standard "T" shaped charging handle, this one is charged from the side with your non shooting hand, so that you never even have to shift your grip. The charging side handle is also reversible so that you can easily move it to the other side in case your are left handed. The bolt release is a factory installed "Phase 5" extended bolt release so that you can release the bolt with your trigger finger also without shifting your grip. The trigger is milspec.
All of the furniture is factory installed "B5 Systems" Flat Dark Earth. The slim handguard has keymod cuts so you can mount anything you want on it. The trigger guard is extended so that you can easily fit gloved fingers in there. The barrel is 5.56 Nato spec 16" M4 Profile 1/7 twist chrome lined. It is chambered in 5.56 so you can also shoot 223. The flash hider is A2 milspec. I watched several videos on these rifles and they said that these rifles digest anything you feed them including cheap steel ammo which is why I bought it in case the "poop hits the fan" and you can only find cheap ammo. It will come with the factory included new in wrapper "C-Products" magazine, owner's manual, lock, and box.
I purchased this brand new from Academy a year to a year and a half ago to shoot carbine matches with and I never did. It is just taking up space in my safe so I am looking to either sell or trade it. I paid about 1200 dollars for it not including tax and would take $1000 for it. title: For Sale:   Ruger Vaquero Birdshead Case Hardened
postcontent: Up for sale is an ultra rare Ruger single action...more on the rare part in a minute.  This is a large frame (original Vaquero), not the current "New Vaquero" model.  The large frame originals are capable of "Ruger only" loads.  It's the blued model with Ruger's faux case hardened frame.  The revolver exhibits a slight turn line on the cylinder from handling but has not been fired outside of the Ruger factory.  The model number is 00511 and the catalog number is BNVBH-453.  Now the backstory on the rare part....Ruger transitioned from the original Vaquero to the new Vaquero late 2004 early 2005 timeframe and stopped making the originals.  Thus gun was made in April of 2010 (based on the spent shell casing that came with it from the factory), 5 years after the end of production and 5 years after Ruger stopped the faux case hardening on their blued single actions.  Furthermore, the notorious Ruger warning label on the barrel was much smaller and on the underside of the barrel.  Prior examples were larger and on the side of the barrel.  After acquiring, I called Ruger to verify the manufacter date.  Between that and the model/catalog number (which were unique to this particular gun), I was able to find out through a few searches this was one of Ruger's parts clean up releases that were only sold through Davidson's, and that there were likely less than 200 or so made.  The late production alone makes it a Ruger collector's object of desire, but the barrel warning label variation puts it over the top.   If interested, feel free to reply with your number.  I'd be happy to text additional pictures, including the factory label showing model/catalog as well as the dated spent casing.    Price is $600
